The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 7: Foreign companies providing connectivity and other technical services to domestic call centres are liable to pay tax on their income in India. According to a decision by the Income Tax Appellate Tribunal in two cases filed by Hyderabad-based Frontline Software and Call World Technologies, the domestic call centres have to deduct tax at source on payments made to foreign companies on support services from abroad.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 7: IDBI Bank is considering a merger or sale of its wholly owned subsidiary IDBI Homefinance by the end of this fiscal, a top official of the bank said. The banks board is likely to take a decision on the matter by the end of March next year, the official said.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 7: The RBI is expected to give up its opposition to the proposal of a monthly compilation and release of inflation data with D. Subbarao moving to the central bank from the finance ministry, which was open to the idea of a shift in the time table of the wholesale price index.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 7: The Kotak group will pick up a majority stake in Ahmedabad Commodity Exchange. The regional stock exchange has sought clearance from the Forward Markets Commission for the stake sale. After the Anil Ambani group and Indiabulls, the Kotak group will become the third company to have a stake in a commodity bourse.                            
	 Calcutta, Sept. 7: West Bengal Power Development Corporation (WBPDCL)will seek international bids for the 1,320MW power project at Sagardighi in Bengal by mid-September, company managing director S. Mahapatra said.                                                                                                                         
